OL,3,CWelsh Council apologises after binman
OL,4,Cthrew batteries in resident's hedge
OL,6,FDenbighshire County Council has
OL,7,Fapologised after one of the council's
OL,8,Fwaste workers threw batteries into a
OL,9,Fresident's hedge.
OL,11,FIn September, Adam Wroz from
OL,12,FLlangollen put the batteries in an
OL,13,Fappropriate recycling box to be
OL,14,Fcollected by the council.
OL,16,FHowever, Mr Wroz discovered the
OL,17,Fbatteries in a hedge in his garden.
