OL,3,CWelsh Council apologises after binman
OL,4,Cthrew batteries in resident's hedge
OL,6,F"I was tidying up that lawn and, as I
OL,7,Fwas strimming it, I found some
OL,8,Fbatteries just on the edge of that
OL,9,Ffence. As I start picking them up, I
OL,10,Fsee there's more and more of them on
OL,11,Fthe other side of the fence, and it
OL,12,Ftook me a minute or so and I realised
OL,13,Fthey're my own batteries that I put in
OL,14,Fthe recycling bin."
OL,16,F"Unacceptable"
OL,18,FDenbighshire County Council has
OL,19,Fapologised for the incident after Adam
OL,20,Fsent a complaint with the video
OL,21,Fevidence to the council.
