OL,3,CWelsh Council apologises after binman
OL,4,Cthrew batteries in resident's hedge
OL,6,FMr Parry has received hundreds of
OL,7,Fcomplaints about the waste service
OL,8,Fover the past few months.
OL,10,F"I've had more complaints about this
OL,11,Fsystem than anything I've had since
OL,12,FI've been on the council since 2012,"
OL,13,Fsaid Mr Parry.
OL,15,F"The rubbish is just building up. I
OL,16,Fthink everyone has a responsibility to
OL,17,Fdo this but after they have gone to
OL,18,Fthe effort to change the system we
OL,19,Fexpect the county to also make the
OL,20,Feffort to be able to collect the
OL,21,Fwaste."
